        </table>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">That for the payment of the Yearly Interest and the redeemings or liquidations to be done in consequence of the above mentioned drawing of which a due publication shall be made by advertisement in the Public News papers, the Honourable appearer in his aforesaid Quality and thus in the name of the United states of America promises and engages to remit the necessary moneys thereto to the above mentioned Gentlemen Messieurs Wilhem &amp; Jan Willink, Nicolaas &amp; Jacob Van Staphorst and De La Lande &amp; Fynje, and their Successors in good bills of exchange products of America or in ready money without any abatement or deduction.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">That this Obligation shall likewise never be subject to any Impost or Taxes imposed or yet to be imposed in the United States of America or any of them, and there shall also never be made or formed by the aforesaid United states of America, or any of them in particular any resolution or Convention whereby the execution and performance hereof should in any manner be prejudiced or hindered though it even were, which the Almighty forbid that any war Hostility or Alienation might arise between the United States of America or any of them on the one hand, and the States of these Lands or any of them on the other hand but on the Contrary that in all circumstances without any exception the contents of these presents shall be punctually performed and executed.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Finally that the Honourable appearer in his abovewritten Quality promises and engages, that this obligation or Bond shall be as Speedily as possible ratifyed and approved by the abovementioned United states of America in Congress assembled, and that the
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0084">[84<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0084.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
original act of this ratification and approbation with an authentic Copy Translation of the same, together with an engrossed copy hereof, shall be deposited in the Custody of a Notary Public in Amsterdam, to be there kept all together, for the satisfaction and security of the money lenders, and to remain there so long untill the Capital and Interest of the borrowed moneys, as likewise the obligations or bonds arising from the drawing as is herebefore appointed and limited be perfectly acquitted and discharged.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">On Failure of a Punctual discharging or acquitting of the Capital as well as the Interest at the appointed periods the whole Capital, or that part of the same which shall at that time be unpaid may by the Gentlemen directors in behalf of the then jointly Money lenders be demanded, and the Honourable appearers abovementioned Principals the United States of America, shall in that case be held and obliged in promptis to discharge and acquit the due Capital with the Interests and charges the whole in one Sum.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">For the accomplishment and performance of all the above written the Honourable appearer binds in his above mentioned quality and thus in the Names and on the part of the United States of America, jointly and each of them Separately as also all their Lands, Chattels, Revenues and Products together with the Imposts and taxes already imposed or hereafter to be imposed and levyed and thus of all the United States and of each of them in particular, in Solidum, and for the whole.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">He the Honourable appearer renouncing in the Names above mentioned to that and expressly and premeditatedly Beneficium Divisionis, together with de duobus vel pluribus reis debendi,<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0006" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0006-ptr">6</a> Signifying a retribution of debts, and that when two or more are indebted, each of them can Satisfy with the payment of his portion; the Honourable appearer promising in his above mentioned quality never to have recourse to the said or to any other Evasion or Subterfuge whatsoever.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Thus done and passed att the Hague in the presence of Francis John Bosboom and John Philip Van Ogten, Witnesses.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">The Original is duly signed.</p>
        <div class="closer">
          <div class="signed-multiple">
    <p class="signed multiple">(:understood:)<br/>Quod Attestor<br/>Signed<br/>L: Sythoff<br/>Not<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">s:</span> Pub<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">c:</span><br/>[SEAL]</p>
  </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0085">[85<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0085.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
      <div class="docback">
        <div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-sn">
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ duplicate ]">Dupl</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>); endorsed: Ratification 1. Feb. 1785 / of / my Loan of 9. March 1784. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ triplicate ]">Tripl</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>). <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ file copy (Ordinarily a copy of a letter retained by a correspondent &lt;i&gt;other than an Adams&lt;/i&gt;; for example, Jeffersons press copies and polygraph copies, since all three of the Adams statesmen systematically entered copies of their outgoing letters in letterbooks.) ]">FC</abbr>s in Dutch and English (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>). For additional information regarding this document, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-01-0006" class="document">Descriptive List of Illustrations</a>, No. 3, above.</p>

        </div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0001">1</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">On 9 March Lambert Sythoff notarized three English language texts of the loan contract for transmission to Congress. The notarized <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ file copy (Ordinarily a copy of a letter retained by a correspondent &lt;i&gt;other than an Adams&lt;/i&gt;; for example, Jeffersons press copies and polygraph copies, since all three of the Adams statesmen systematically entered copies of their outgoing letters in letterbooks.) ]">FC</abbr> in English is a copy of the aforementioned documents. The notarized <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ file copy (Ordinarily a copy of a letter retained by a correspondent &lt;i&gt;other than an Adams&lt;/i&gt;; for example, Jeffersons press copies and polygraph copies, since all three of the Adams statesmen systematically entered copies of their outgoing letters in letterbooks.) ]">FC</abbr> in Dutch is of the contract in that language. The consortium wrote <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> on the 11th that it had received the contracts from Sythoff and would send them to America by the vessels getting Ready, to Sease the first Opportunity for their Departure (all <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Manuscripts and other materials, 16391889, in the Adams Manuscript Trust collection given to the Massachusetts Historical Society in 1956 and enlarged by a few additions of family papers since then. Citations in the present edition are simply by date of the original document if the original is in the main chronological series of the Papers and therefore readily found in the microfilm edition of the Adams Papers (see below).&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Adams Papers</span>). The contract printed here is the second of the three copies sent to Congress for ratification and returned to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> with the instrument of ratification attached, both of which were enclosed with the <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0306" class="document">letter from John Jay, dated 11 Feb. 1785</a>, below. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> received it on 2 May, having on 23 April received the original, which he immediately dispatched to the consortium. The triplicate was received later in May (to John Jay, 24 April, 4, 30 May 1785, <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Works of John Adams, Second President of the United States: with a Life of the Author,&lt;/i&gt; ed. Charles Francis Adams, Boston, 18501856; 10 vols. ]">JA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Works,</span></span> 8:236238, 239240, 252254; to the consortium, 24 April 1785, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr>, <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Formerly, Adams Papers, Microfilms. The corpus of the Adams Papers, 16391889, as published on microfilm by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 19541959, in 608 reels. Cited in the present work, when necessary, by reel number. Available in research libraries throughout the United States and in a few libraries in Canada, Europe, and New Zealand.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">APM</span> Reel 107). For an explanation of the almost eleven months that passed between the dispatch of the contract and Congress ratification of it, see the <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0300&amp;expandNote=ADMS-06-16-02-0300-fn-0001#ADMS-06-16-02-0300-fn-0001" class="document">ratification of 1 Feb. 1785, note 1</a>, below.</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0002">2</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">This is a reference to and paraphrase of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s [<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">20 June 1780</span>] commission authorizing him to negotiate a Dutch loan in the absence of Henry Laurens. Originally issued because Laurens departure for Europe had been delayed, it took on new importance after the British captured the South Carolinian on 3 Sept. 1780 and subsequently imprisoned him in the Tower of London. Pieter Galenus van Hole had notarized the 1782 loan contract at Amsterdam (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0278-0001%20ADMS-print-06-09-02-0278-0002%20ADMS-print-06-09-02-0279#ADMS-06-09-02-pb-0452" class="pageNo">9:452453</a>; 10:196; 13:110, 116).</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0003-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0003">3</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Of money not to be paid out.</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0004-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0004">4</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">In the 1782 loan, each bond or obligation was to be Signed b him Honble. Appearer, that is, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, whereas in this loan they were to be signed by the consortium (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0062#ADMS-06-13-02-pb-0114" class="pageNo">13:114</a>).</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0005-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0005">5</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">This was an extremely important provision, for it promised to save the United States substantial interest if implemented, as it was in 1785. Then, rather than issuing  50,000 in new securities that would have earned interest until their redemption in 1801, the United States made a onetime cash payment (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Pieter J. van Winter and James C. Riley, &lt;i&gt;American Finance and Dutch Investment, 1780-1805,&lt;/i&gt; New York, 1977; 2 vols. ]">Winter, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Amer. Finance and Dutch Investment,</span></span> 1:115). For the consortiums proposal to do that, see its <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0203" class="document">letter of 2 Sept. 1784</a>, and for <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s approval of the plan see his reply of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0212" class="document">16 Sept.</a>, both below.</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0006-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0049-fn-0006">6</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">That is, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> renounced the right of one of several borrowers to pay only its prorated share of the debt. Thus each state of the United States was responsible for the entire debt rather than for only a part that might be apportioned to it. The 1782 loan contract contained the same renunciation (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0062#ADMS-06-13-02-pb-0114" class="pageNo">13:114</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0062%20ADMS-print-06-13-02-0063#ADMS-06-13-02-pb-0116" class="pageNo">116</a>).</p>

        </div>

      </div>
